```

We won't modify the existing behavior of the `retrieve` method -- currently, there's a 1:1 mapping between calling this method on any `StripeObject` and sending the equivalent API request and we don't want to break that invariant.

We could add a convenience method on `ListObject`s (e.g. `retrieve_cached` or something) to return the resource without querying the API if it's already in the list, but I don't feel there would be much value in it. Esp. in Python, a simple list comprehension will do the job as you noted.

