You can also avoid the receive with the code below and then delete the message manually when you're ready for that 

``` vhdl
      -- receive(net, bus_handle.p_actor, request_msg);
      wait_for_message(net, bus_handle.p_actor, status);
      get_message(net, bus_handle.p_actor, request_msg);
```

Status is of type `com_status_t` but can be ignored. It's only useful to determine a timeout if you add a timeout parameter to the `get_message` call.

The forwarding just committed doesn't hand over ownership. It just enables you to push a message into another and doesn't set the input to null. This is something I'm considering though. One of the main points with message passing is to avoid mistakes with shared data by making sure that there is only one owner at any time.

